  "text": "These paradoxical observations may be related to differential associations with different stroke subtypes. Several recent studies reported that cholesterol was lowest in cardioembolic strokes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The largest prospective cohort of 4128 adults aged >70 years reported that high or normal/borderline total cholesterol values were associated with good survival compared to low values [CITATION_4] .",
